Draghi: If we had not acted in recent years, the counterfactual would have been a disastrous deflation
Draghi: We first need a stable, solid recovery for inflation to return to its objective
Draghi: We have shown today that we are not short of ammunition
Draghi: If we were to give up, we would have deflation which increases the real value of debt
Draghi: There was a very reassuring, positive, constructive discussion in the Governing Council
Draghi: The majority in favour of this package has been overwhelming
Draghi: We expect a very sizeable take-up for the second TLTRO given the recovery and the very attractive conditions
Draghi: We are confident that we can reach the purchase target of 80 bln for the horizon of the programme
Constâncio: Banks had capital gains as a result of our policies last year
Draghi: The aggretage profitability of the banking system has not been hindered by negative rates
Draghi: Governing Council decided not to introduce a tiered deposit rate
Draghi: The experiences we had with negative rates have been very positive
Draghi: A bank that is very active in lending to the real economy, can borrow more than banks active in other ways
Draghi: Reform efforts need to be stepped up in the majority of euro area countries
Draghi: Annual HICP inflation at 0.1% in 2016 [from 1.0% in Dec], 1.3% in 2017 [from 1.6% in Dec] and 1.6% in 2018
Draghi: Annual real GDP to increase by 1.4% in 2016 [from 1.7% in Dec], 1.7% in 2017 [unchanged from Dec] and 1.8% in 2018
Draghi: It is crucial to avoid second-round effects by securing a return of inflation to levels below, but close to, 2% without undue delay
Draghi: Governing Council expects the key ECB interest rates to remain at present or lower levels well past horizon of net asset purchases
Draghi: For banks whose net lending exceeds a benchmark, the rate of the TLTRO II can be as low as the interest rate on the deposit facility
Draghi: Non-bank investment grade corporate bonds to be part of a new corporate sector purchase programme
Draghi: Package exploits synergies of different instruments; calibrated to further ease financing conditions, stimulate new credit provision
Draghi: Governing Council has decided on a set of measures in the pursuit of its price stability objective
6. A new series of four targeted longer-term refinancing operations (TLTRO II), each with a maturity of four years, will be launched.
5. Investment grade euro-denominated bonds issued by non-bank corporations will be included in the list of assets for regular purchases.
4. The monthly purchases under the asset purchase programme will be expanded to €80 billion starting in April.
3. The interest rate on the deposit facility will be decreased by 10 basis points to -0.40%, with effect from 16 March 2016.
2. The interest rate on the marginal lending facility will be decreased by 5 basis points to 0.25%, with effect from 16 March 2016
1. The interest rate on the MRO will be decreased by 5 basis points to 0.00%, starting from the operation to be settled on 16 March 2016
